{"schema_version": 2, "ts": "2026-05-11T00:00:00Z", "event": "clarify_critic", "feature": "audit-cortex-coreresearch-skill-output-shape-for-token-waste-in-researchmd-sections", "parent_epic_loaded": false, "findings": [{"text": "The assessment rates intent clarity High while the source defers the canonical schema decision to step 2 with three options; the α/β/γ choice is a load-bearing ambiguity that downstream subtasks depend on.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Intent clarity claim leans on the ~3,000 token quantification, but the source itself flags this number as suspect under the problem-only retro template caveat; Adversarial Review at ~1,170 tok is in the keep bucket, so ~39% of claimed waste is contested in the same ticket.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Scope boundedness rated High but Touch points includes 'skills/research/SKILL.md (or wherever /cortex-core:research skill lives — verify path)' — scope cannot be explicit when the primary file under modification is identified only by a parenthetical 'verify path'.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Scope boundedness imports the conditional 'update skills/discovery/references/research.md if it uses the same skill' verbatim without resolving it; a conditional touch point is by definition unbounded scope, and the assessment also doesn't enumerate the cross-cutting effect on /cortex-core:lifecycle itself.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Requirements alignment claim cites no specific clauses from the five requirements documents named; 'no conflicts detected' is asserted, not demonstrated, and the principles quoted are reusable boilerplate that would justify nearly any cleanup ticket.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Verification criterion 'Net per-feature research.md token cost reduces by ≥40%' is incompatible with α (codify de facto schema → approximately zero reduction); the contradiction between offering α as valid and a 40% target as acceptance gate should have dragged intent clarity or scope boundedness below High.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Criticality High leans on '/cortex-core:research is shared infrastructure and its output shape is a contract that other skills depend on' but the source explicitly says '0 downstream consumers' for at least one section and uses 'no programmatic consumer' as keep/cut evidence; the contract-strength claim is overstated.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The methodological move of treating γ as 'unvalidated hypothesis' under the clarify protocol's note effectively excludes the largest open question in the ticket from the scope assessment; an undecided α/β/γ choice is not scope-neutral when steps 3, 4, and verification all branch on its outcome.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The 'What to land' five-subtasks-with-clear-deliverables claim is asserted at higher resolution than the source supports: sample size jumps from 5 (epic-172-audit) to ≥10 without justification, and inventory acceptance criteria beyond the four-section worked example are unspecified.", "origin": "primary"}], "dispositions": {"apply": 2, "dismiss": 7, "ask": 0}, "applied_fixes": ["Revised requirements alignment narrative to cite specific project.md clauses ('Workflow trimming', 'Complexity must earn its place', 'Maintainability through simplicity', 'ROI matters') and to record that multi-agent.md/observability.md/pipeline.md/remote-access.md were scanned with grep for research-skill-output-shape constraints and none were found (only an unrelated documentation note in observability.md:145).", "Sharpened the clarified intent statement to acknowledge the ≥40% verification target presupposes β/γ — α is retained as a fallback option but the expected path is alignment-via-cleanup, not alignment-via-codification."], "dismissals": [{"finding_index": 0, "rationale": "Clarify protocol §1 explicitly classifies implementation suggestions as unvalidated hypotheses for research, not as ambiguous intent. The clarified-intent goal 'audit current emission, decide canonical schema, align implementation' is well-formed; the α/β/γ decision is the work product of Research/Spec, not a precondition for entering them."}, {"finding_index": 1, "rationale": "The ~3,000 token number is approximate motivation; the audit subtask itself produces the refined number. Intent clarity does not depend on the motivation figure being precise, and the source flags its own caveats — the ticket is self-aware about evidence quality."}, {"finding_index": 2, "rationale": "Verified during clarify: skills/research/SKILL.md exists. The parenthetical 'verify path' is overly cautious authoring, not a real unresolved touch point."}, {"finding_index": 3, "rationale": "Verified during clarify: skills/discovery/references/research.md exists. The 'if' phrasing bounds scope to 'wherever /cortex-core:research is referenced,' which Research enumerates as part of its codebase analysis. /cortex-core:lifecycle's reference at skills/lifecycle/references/research.md is already named as a touch point."}, {"finding_index": 6, "rationale": "The '0 downstream consumers' in the ticket refers to programmatic readers of specific research.md sections (e.g., 'Requirements & Constraints' has no code reading it), not to skill-level invocation dependencies. /cortex-core:research is invoked by both /cortex-core:lifecycle and /cortex-core:discovery, making it shared infrastructure. High criticality applies per the clarify §5 default rule for skill/agentic-layer changes."}, {"finding_index": 7, "rationale": "Same basis as Finding 1's dismissal: the clarify protocol's §1 note explicitly addresses prescriptive ticket bodies. The α/β/γ decision is the canonical product of Research+Spec; deferring it does not make Clarify-stage scope ambiguous."}, {"finding_index": 8, "rationale": "Acceptance-criteria refinement is the Spec phase's job. 'Inventory of ≥10 samples' is a sufficient deliverable name at Clarify resolution; Spec will tighten what makes the inventory complete and justify the sample-size bump from 5 to ≥10."}], "status": "ok"}
